author: Shane Forsey
reviewBody: Superb University with amazing facilities. If you get a chance to go here, don't hesitate.
name: University of Limerick

author: Ernesto Baez
reviewBody: What an amazing place. The campus is absolutely beautiful very safe and transport directly to and from Dublin. Our dorms were right next the river/creek and we could hear the birds signing all the time. At nights the campus can be so enchanting with a slight drizzle that never seems to get you wet you, with a fog so dense you can barely see 2 meters in-front of you. The facilities are first class and my experience with the staff and fellow student body was nothing short lifelong memories.
name: University of Limerick

author: Martin Rathfelder
reviewBody: Very spacious. very green.
name: University of Limerick

author: Love Nature
reviewBody: Beautiful place surrounded by natural beauty with river and natural vegetations. Accessible : with bus stop for buses going and arriving from dublin and limerick city , easy and comfortable to walk throughout or to 🚴‍♀️ and briges connecting different part of university. Beautiful compound and facilities : unique buildings, bridges , parking for cars and bikes, shops, café , sport fields and facilities, river sides with beautiful walking routes.
name: University of Limerick

author: Colin McInerney
reviewBody: Amazing campus.. there is many different locations to go walking within the grounds.. very scenic place that offers something for everyone.. the college itself is a very prestigious school and a very well known landmark in the limerick area.
name: University of Limerick

author: David Mc Namara
reviewBody: There's a beautiful walk along the river between the University and the city
name: University of Limerick

author: Da Dark Force
reviewBody: I was at the Arena for a swimming competition , I absolutely loved it, great facilities, great pool and a lovely walk around the facility. As for the University itself as I do not go to it I can not tell you how good the education is but from what people say it is very good, its entire campus/ its accommodation villages are no smoking. Its parks and buildings are very well kept, the only little bluff, if you are going here do not forget to book your accommodation early so you have a wider choice, thank you for reading.
name: University of Limerick

author: Jorge Baptista
reviewBody: Lovely walks around the campus along the river and over the bridges.

author: TRAVEL JOY & PEACE
reviewBody: Great University of entire country.. Spread over 800 acres .... Lush green landscape.... My God!! The beautiful fairy tale River Shanon ... The ornament like bridge .... So grand grand gaalaa grounds.... Strong and secure buildings ..... Above all the education level....really fantastic great and five star 🌟 category educational institution that no longer delay in choosing it will make the parents regret latter... Make it a decision to enroll son and daughter here....🎖✨️

author: Fatima Nasser
reviewBody: Very Beautiful and Spacious Campus. The Shannon River passes through the University which makes it more fascinating.
name: University of Limerick

author: Mayank Srivastava
reviewBody: A great place to study and attain the necessary skills to succeed in professional life. You'll also make friends from several countries. The campus is massive and it might take a while before you can fully explore every corner of the University. The University is also the modern amenities and facilities. It has an excellent library and a great gym. The faculty and staff are extremely helpful.
name: University of Limerick

author: mahdi nohtani
reviewBody: The campus is beautiful. It is open to public and it is a great place for socialising. The living bridge over shannon river is amazing. It is combination of nature with human architecture.
name: University of Limerick

author: chima Njemanze
reviewBody: Excellent university village. Very cozy academic environment. away from the city hussle and bustle. A perfect university set up
name: University of Limerick

author: Michael Quinn
reviewBody: Excellent scenery with beautiful walking areas, providing an enriching experience.
name: University of Limerick

author: Marian English
reviewBody: My wife and I have been to UCH Limerick on several occasions and have enjoyed many performances through the years. The concert hall is spacious and warm with excellent disability facilities. The staff are courteous and helpful. Tonight, we went to see Rebecca Storm in concert. We arrived at 7.40pm and 10 minutes later we were still trying to find a free parking space.The main car park was full. We were unable to access the other car parks as entry was blocked by a lowered barrier. This was annoying and disappointing. Our advice is to arrive earlier than usual to secure your parking. UCH is an excellent venue to attend concerts. The acoustics are superb. We will be back.
name: University of Limerick

author: Padraig Glynn
reviewBody: Beautiful campus. Wonderful faculty. Great courses. Well worth attending for a programme or just a visit
name: University of Limerick
